&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;Position Summary&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Test Coordinator is responsible for planning, coordinating, and governing testing activities across the technology delivery lifecycle, with a strong emphasis on Technical Testing (Unit, CIT, System) &amp;amp; System Integration Testing (SIT). The role ensures all stakeholders are effectively supported to validate solutions, testing activities are aligned to the integrated programme plan, and risks, dependencies, and progress are clearly managed and reported.&amp;nbsp;The Test Coordinator operates within the technology teams and across the Quality capability on the programme, providing structure, visibility, and control over testing activities. The role focuses on enabling technology testing, ensuring up and down stream testing outcomes are understood, and confirming solutions are fit for purpose prior to release.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Understanding of Testing Activities Supporting Technology Value Streams&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Test Coordinator understands the detailed technical testing and end-to-end testing activities required to enable effective SIT and ensures these activities are coordinated, visible, and aligned to delivery of the technical solution to enable end-to-end validation.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Testing Scope and Readiness&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;Understands overall testing scope, environments, roles, timelines, and entry and exit criteria to ensure all test phases are planned realistically and aligned to the integrated programme plan.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;SIT Preparation Inputs&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;Ensures business-focused test scenarios, test data, access, and supporting materials are in place so the tech teams can execute SIT efficiently and with confidence.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Upstream Testing Outcomes&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;Provides and interprets Unit, System and Integration testing results to confirm SIT readiness, identify residual risks, and prevent SIT being impacted by unresolved technical issues.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;SIT Coordination and Execution&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;Plans and coordinates SIT activities, supports Integration testers, tracks execution progress, and ensures issues and blockers are managed promptly.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Results, Risks, and Sign-off&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;Consolidates SIT outcomes, defects, and risks to support informed Technology sign-off and E2E/UAT readiness decisions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt

